e_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1691401079 320w" width="1680" height="1120" alt="The importance of mental health awareness in early years - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="The importance of mental health awareness in early years - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-23_"/></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-11e7" data-category="Generic Content" data-name="Matcha" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-dBFCZX khzvmY pf-24_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gvPcJq dRaLso"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-25_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-26_"><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-27_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-29_">Early childhood is a critical period in a person's life. The experiences during these years significantly influence an individual's future, shaping their physical, intellectual, and emotional development. Therefore, mental health awareness in early years is not just an important topic; it's a necessary one.<br><br>In this blog, we will delve into the importance of mental health awareness and why taking this course is a must-have for anyone in contact with children in the early years.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-30_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-32_">Recognising the need for mental health awareness in early years</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Recognising_the_need_for_mental_health_awareness_in_early_years_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1691401130" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Recognising_the_need_for_mental_health_awareness_in_early_years_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1691401130 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Recognising_the_need_for_mental_health_awareness_in_early_years_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1691401130 320w" width="2279" height="1520" alt="Recognising the need for mental health awareness in early years - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Recognising the need for mental health awareness in early years - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-33_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-34_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-36_">The Mandatory Training Group has developed a crucial "Mental Health Awareness in Early Years" course as part of the <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/products/wellbeing-and-emotional-needs-coordinator-wenco-online-training-package?variant=39471535161413" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">Wellbeing and Emotional Needs Coordinator (WENCO)</span></i></a> pack of training courses. This course is designed with a core belief that every educational setting should have a person responsible for ensuring all children's emotional needs and overall well-being.<br><br>In nurturing these aspects, we're cultivating a healthier, more constructive environment where children can flourish and reach their full potential.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-37_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-39_">Understanding mental health in early years</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understanding_mental_health_in_the_early_years_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1691401194" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understanding_mental_health_in_the_early_years_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1691401194 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understanding_mental_health_in_the_early_years_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1691401194 320w" width="1880" height="1254" alt="Understanding mental health in the early years - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Understanding mental health in the early years - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-40_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-41_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-43_">In essence, mental health awareness involves comprehending what mental health means, recognising signs and symptoms of potential issues, and understanding how to support children in managing their stresses and anxieties. It is integral to children's learning and development. As children grow, their physical and academic progress must be monitored alongside their emotional well-being.<br><br>Mental health refers not only to the absence of mental disorders but also to a state where individuals can realise their abilities, cope with normal life stresses, work productively, and contribute to their community. It's about thriving, not just surviving.<br> </span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-44_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-46_">Signs and symptoms</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Signs_and_symptoms_Mental_health_awareness_in_the_early_years_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1691401270" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Signs_and_symptoms_Mental_health_awareness_in_the_early_years_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1691401270 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Signs_and_symptoms_Mental_health_awareness_in_the_early_years_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1691401270 320w" width="1354" height="903" alt="Signs and symptoms Mental health awareness in the early years - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Signs and symptoms Mental health awareness in the early years - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-47_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-48_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-50_">Identifying mental health issues in children can be challenging, as the symptoms can often mimic typical developmental stages. However, prolonged or extreme signs can indicate a problem.<br><br>Symptoms can include consistent difficulty concentrating, excessive worry or anxiety, persistent nightmares, drastic changes in academic performance, or persistent disobedience and aggression.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-51_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-53_">Support and care strategies</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Children_s_mental_and_emotional_health_Support_and_care_strategies_in_the_early_years_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1691401334" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Children_s_mental_and_emotional_health_Support_and_care_strategies_in_the_early_years_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1691401334 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Children_s_mental_and_emotional_health_Support_and_care_strategies_in_the_early_years_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1691401334 320w" width="339" height="226" alt="Children’s mental and emotional health Support and care strategies in the early years - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Children’s mental and emotional health Support and care strategies in the early years - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-54_"/><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-55_" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Understanding mental health issues is only the first step; knowing how to support children grappling with these challenges is equally critical. The <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/products/mental-health-awareness-in-the-early-years-online-cpduk-accredited?variant=39462294487109" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 20